snippet.textDisplay: Right now, there are people all over the world who are just like you. They're either lonely, they're missing somebody, they're depressed, they're hurt, they're scarred from the past, they're having personal issues no one knows about, they have secrets you wouldn't believe. They wish, they dream and they hope. And right now, they are sitting here reading these words, and I'm writing this for you so you dont feel alone anymore. Always remember, don't be depressed about the past, don't worry about the future, and just focus on today. If today's not so great don't worry! Tomorrow's a new chance. If you are reading this, be sure to share this around to make others feel better. Have a nice day! :)

snippet.textDisplay: This clip caught my attention as if it called me to listen to the paragraphs of the written comments. I cried from the intensity of their tenderness. I am very happy that there are people from different parts of the world who share the same phrases and kindness in varying degrees. Their words are touching and from the depths. I also wanted to share with you something of myself in this loss that I live in, and it seems at first glance to be eternal. I also know that there are people who feel the same as I do, so I would like to tell you not to be sad, you are not alone, and that I love you and I hope As my words embrace you, while I am writing, I feel happy and want to cry. However, I feel that there is something magical waiting for me and waiting for you, my beloved. So live with all love. As the moon lights up the night and the stars decorate the sky, I am certain that after this annihilation that I feel, there is something that will shine deep within me, just as it will shine deep within you, my beloved. All my love, gratitude and warm hugs to you and me. May God's blessings and mine accompany you. Maam Noor was from the other half of the world, in the continent of Asia, specifically in Iraq. ğŸ˜Šâ¤

snippet.textDisplay:
There is a sense of familiarity in this whole clip. I'm reminiscing my  younger self, how life was curiously fascinating,  how i was connected to my core, i had it all when i didn't know half of reality i have  slowly experienced and learned about. 
This is maybe a reminder , that  we are all very small fragile living things in the planet earth , so to live well as this small living thing we must not disconnect ourselves from our own little worlds our very own realities.

snippet.textDisplay: I want to leave a message here. Hi, you who read this message must be tired of the world, you are not alone , because I also feel tired of this world, with my life too. There are many obstacles to go through, pain, sadness, disappointment, anger comes every day. Sometimes the desire arises to Stop. But there is always a reason to hold on. I, you and all of you are amazing, thank you for choosing to continue living. I love you all, and the people you meet by chance or the people you know with your silly antics or with your kindness that makes them happy.Make them smile or laugh, I and they are grateful for your presence in this world. Life is sometimes unfair. Stay healthy, guys, and stay a good person. â¤ May God always protect us, and lift our sorrows and difficulties aamiin ğŸ¤²

snippet.textDisplay: Thank you for this.  I used to message my mom before she would go to sleep when she was ill, and auto correct always changed mom to moon.  So I started calling her "Moon". This is what I would ask her, "How was your day?" After talking for a little while she would say, "I'm going to bed now. Thank you for always being there for me. Good night dear."  Oh how I miss my mom, my moon.  I love you and miss you mom, always. ğŸ˜”ğŸ’”

snippet.textDisplay: you feel alone, rejected by others, you think you are a ghost sometimes, you say to yourself why no one pays attention to me and yet I am nice you ask yourself these kinds of questions because you think the world is unfair to you, and you see people who are happy around you and you dream of having their life and you tell yourself why it doesn't happen to you, and when you are happy you tell yourself it won't last, you know how long you have lost, we ask you the same questions every day, all these questions that have destroyed you from the inside and that have destroyed you... but you never asked yourself where your place was and with whom you would feel better , you seem lost in space, and sometimes you want to escape by listening to soft music, and you have no one to share your little life, because you think a lot of people have judged you badly, so why don't you change your life, because you experienced a tragedy, because you separated from the one you love and it upset you...and you look for shoulders to cry on, you must move forward whatever happens you don't have no choice, all these failures, all these people you meet in your life are stages that you will cross throughout, so get up and stop feeling sorry for yourself..down with you for raising your head, down with you until 'at the end, what is worth living for?

snippet.textDisplay:
Most days I feel like I deserve to die. I don't contribute to anyone's happiness. Holding down a job is so difficult, and I feel my continued existence pains my friends and family. Mom, if you ever see this, I'm sorry I was never the son you wanted. I'm sorry I couldn't do what you needed me to be since Dad passed. I wish I was better. 

To my sister, the one who was always there for me. I'm sorry I couldn't be the brother to help you. I hate myself the most for never stepping up to the plate for our family, and as a result a lot of it fell to you. Seeing you do so great has made me so happy, and yet I feel like if I wasn't around anymore, you'd be free from having to cover for me so many, many times. 

I can't talk to anyone about how I'm slowing inching towards death with every passing day. I wish I had an inkling of hope for the future, but honestly, every decent future my family has, I never imagine myself in it. 

Someone, anyone, please save me. I just want to go back to how I felt when I was younger. When I felt like the future was a place I had to get to as soon as possible. When happiness was a trip to the convenience store. When Dad was still around. 

Little me, I'm sorry for letting you down too. You were a great kid. I really messed you up.

snippet.textDisplay:
Perempuan kecil itu melewati banyak masa suram sendirian. Dia sendiri tidak tau kemana dia akan berpulang. Semua jalan yg dia lewati sudah hilang dan terhapus kenangan, tidak lagi sama seperti dulu dan tidak bisa kembali pulang. Jalan satu satunya adalah membuat hal baru, harapan baru, dan keinginan baru. Dia menyadari ada banyak jalan yg belum dia lewati dan dia mengetahui bahwa dia sendiri. Terkadang tanpa tujuan, dia ingin berdoa tapi hatinya bimbang menentukan keputusan dan jalan yg akan dia ambil. Satu satunya yg bisa menyelamatkannya adalah bulan. Dia sering memandangi langit malam dan bintang berharap keajaiban itu datang dalam hidupnya, dan dia tidak menyadari itu. Mungkin dia lelah dengan keadaan, dan ingin kembali bersama orang yg dia kasihi. Namun sayangnya dia sudah berpulang, yg bisa dia lihat hanya bintang bintang kecil itu. 

Satu satunya harapnnya untuk hidup mungkin yg tersisa hanya satu.

Kini dia sendiri menatap langit petang itu sendirian dan berharap harapannya dapat terkabul oleh penciptanya.

â¤

snippet.textDisplay:
Terkadang ketika kamu jatuh cinta kamu akan sering memberontak daripada bertahan. Kenapa ada seseorang yg lebih mencintai kekasihnya namun masih bertahan ditempat yg sama saat kekasihnya bilang diam disitu. Apa itu menunjukkan ketulusannya terhadap seseorang yg dia cintai? 

Menahan perasaan itu sulit dilakukan ketika kamu jatuh cinta, kenapa kamu harus berdiam diri dan memandangi oranglain jauh disana hanya dari kejauhan bukankah itu menyakitkan untukmu sendiri? Kamu bahkan tidak tau perasaan seseorang yg kamu cintai sebelum kamu menanyakan dan menemuinya langsung. 

Cinta itu sebuah pengorbanan, namun terkadang cinta memang harus mempertahankan satu sama lain.

The Moon

It's late, but my heart is still in turmoil. I look up at the sky, and there you are, Moon, watching over me with your gentle gaze. Have you already understood my thoughts, even though I havenâ€™t asked for your empathy?

Iâ€™ve poured so much effort into making my life feel less meaningless...,trying to figure out how to live without wasting this precious time weâ€™re given.

Moon, sometimes life feels like a dreamâ€”one where all the things that tie me down suddenly seem so light, and Iâ€™m left unsure of what the right way to live even is.

I wonder, Moon, where did we come from, why do we stay, and what causes us to fall apart and disappear? Honestly, I canâ€™t even begin to explain the pain and confusion Iâ€™ve felt, lost in this endless uncertainty.

And yet, Moon, Iâ€™ve reached a point where I feel like Iâ€™ve become nothing, and somehow, thatâ€™s lifted an invisible weight off my shoulders. I no longer need to cling to any identity or play any role. Itâ€™s freeing. When night falls, I escape this earthly world, merging with the universe, with the source of everything.

Oh Moon, how absurd it all seemsâ€”the things people do, the stories they tell. They argue about the 'conflicts' happening in the world, neatly dividing whatâ€™s good and whatâ€™s evil, whoâ€™s right and whoâ€™s wrong. I donâ€™t know what to do except play my part in this life, knowing full well that everyone has a role to play, and so do I. I have a role, but when night comes, I let go of it, so I can recharge my soul.

I know everything is just a dream, but it still breaks my heart when my fellow actors get hurt in this dream. I feel for them, and the hardships their roles bring. But what can I do? Life hands us a role, and we have to fulfil it.

Who am I supposed to be? What should I become?

All my worries, fears, and joys feel light now like theyâ€™re evaporating into the air. With my eyes closed, I feel my soul more clearly than ever, along with its divine guidance.

I have nothing to lose, so I must give it my all.

Thank you, Moon, for listening to my thoughts, from someone without a name.
